The paper deals with the analysis of online learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the high-dimensional scaling limit of these algorithms, which involves concepts from information theory and numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves the analysis of a nonlinear PDE, which falls under the subfield of scientific computing (cs.SI) and the use of stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in data science (cs.DS).
